WEBVTT

00:01.369 --> 00:03.537
ANNOUNCER: Thanks for
downloading this Fox show.

00:03.571 --> 00:05.739
And don't miss
all-new episodes on Fox.

00:08.609 --> 00:10.178
Previously on Empire...
ANDRE:
Rhonda!

00:10.211 --> 00:11.579
(sobbing):
Andre messed up.

00:11.612 --> 00:13.414
Andre did mess up.

00:13.447 --> 00:15.549
What's your half brother Tariq
doing here?

00:15.583 --> 00:16.650
I know Lucious married Anika

00:16.684 --> 00:18.018
just to keep her
from testifying.

00:18.052 --> 00:19.087
If I can prove
that the marriage

00:19.120 --> 00:20.688
is fake, I can subpoena her.

00:20.721 --> 00:22.890
I know we're still good
as long as I see

00:22.923 --> 00:24.358
that fire in your eye.
What me and you had

00:24.392 --> 00:25.859
is dead.

00:25.893 --> 00:27.061
(breathing heavily)

00:27.095 --> 00:29.163
COOKIE:
Get yourself together.

00:29.197 --> 00:31.765
She is out there
taking your song.

00:31.799 --> 00:34.568
LUCIOUS:
We're gonna show
all these haters

00:34.602 --> 00:36.204
how dark hell can get.

00:37.037 --> 00:39.039
(doorbell chimes)

00:43.877 --> 00:45.879
(doorbell chimes)

00:48.382 --> 00:49.583
(doorbell chimes)

00:49.617 --> 00:51.085
*

00:54.622 --> 00:55.889
Thanks.

01:02.430 --> 01:04.232
(doorbell chimes)

01:08.269 --> 01:09.503
Thank you.

01:19.180 --> 01:20.881
PORSHA:
Cookie!

01:20.914 --> 01:22.816
Cookie, you gotta come see this,
Cookie!

01:22.850 --> 01:24.518
Would you shut up
all that noi...

01:26.520 --> 01:27.788
Oh, hell no.

01:27.821 --> 01:29.056
Uh-uh. Out.

01:29.089 --> 01:30.324
Take it out. All of it.

01:30.358 --> 01:31.159
What?

01:31.192 --> 01:32.393
Take it out.

01:32.426 --> 01:33.927
All right, get it,
get it out of here.

01:33.961 --> 01:35.329
You sure?
All of it?

01:35.363 --> 01:36.664
We can't keep
the espresso machine,

01:36.697 --> 01:38.098
a couple Jimmy Choos
or nothing?

01:38.132 --> 01:39.800
Out! All of it!

01:39.833 --> 01:41.902
That damn Lucious
needs to stop.

01:41.935 --> 01:43.437
I'm done with his ass.

01:43.471 --> 01:45.473
*

01:52.713 --> 01:54.148
WOMAN: Mm-hmm.
ANIKA: Um...

01:54.182 --> 01:55.916
Bella's a preemie,
and so she's gonna need

01:55.949 --> 01:57.151
some specific
attention.

01:57.185 --> 01:58.652
WOMAN:
Yes.

01:58.686 --> 02:00.488
How do you handle
stressful situations?

02:00.521 --> 02:02.990
Well, I assess
the baby's needs.

02:03.023 --> 02:06.494
Does she need to be fed,
or burped,

02:06.527 --> 02:08.996
or should I pick her up and...
LUCIOUS:
Wait. Hold on, hold on.

02:09.029 --> 02:10.431
Who in the hell are
all these people in my house?

02:10.464 --> 02:12.132
Oh, my God.

02:12.166 --> 02:13.301
Up, up, up, up, up.
Out. Come on.

02:13.334 --> 02:14.535
I'm sorry,
the interview's over.

02:14.568 --> 02:15.969
Out. Ladies!

02:16.003 --> 02:18.038
Ladies! Out!
I don't need a nanny.

02:18.071 --> 02:19.540
(Anika sighs)
LUCIOUS:
I said go!

02:19.573 --> 02:21.509
Lucious...
Get the hell out of here.

02:21.542 --> 02:23.244
Come on!

02:24.745 --> 02:27.615
Who gave you the permission
to hire a nanny?

02:27.648 --> 02:29.550
I need permission?

02:29.583 --> 02:30.818
In my house, you do.

02:30.851 --> 02:32.052
Or have you forgotten

02:32.085 --> 02:33.521
that the only reason you in here

02:33.554 --> 02:36.156
is because of that damn
federal investigation?

02:36.190 --> 02:37.658
I don't need people I don't know

02:37.691 --> 02:39.159
looking in my life, okay?

02:39.193 --> 02:40.394
(Bella crying)

02:40.428 --> 02:41.795
Oh, my God, Lucious,

02:41.829 --> 02:43.364
I need help.

02:43.397 --> 02:45.132
Okay? I cannot
do this by myself!

02:45.165 --> 02:47.868
I took care of Dwight
all on my own.

02:47.901 --> 02:49.136
I'll get Bella.

02:49.169 --> 02:50.504
No!

02:50.538 --> 02:51.972
You keep your crazy hands

02:52.005 --> 02:53.674
off of my baby.
You know what you're gonna do?

02:53.707 --> 02:55.042
You got one job
in this house,

02:55.075 --> 02:56.477
and that's a mother.

02:56.510 --> 02:58.746
Get in there and
do your damn job.

02:58.779 --> 03:01.014
(Bella continues crying)

03:01.048 --> 03:03.150
ANGELA YEE:
And we are back, peoples.

03:03.183 --> 03:04.518
And today we've got

03:04.552 --> 03:06.654
Jamal Lyon and City Councilman

03:06.687 --> 03:08.322
Angelo Dubois
in the building

03:08.356 --> 03:10.491
and we're talking about
violence in hip hop.

03:10.524 --> 03:12.726
Now, there's a question
that we've all been

03:12.760 --> 03:15.396
dancing around,
so I gotta ask:

03:15.429 --> 03:18.832
Jamal, at the Empire XStream
launch party, what happened?

03:18.866 --> 03:21.535
It looked like you
froze up onstage.
JAMAL:
No, I didn't freeze up.

03:21.569 --> 03:23.437
That's not what happened.
Well, was it something

03:23.471 --> 03:25.706
to do with you getting shot?
Because...

03:25.739 --> 03:27.708
PTSD is nothing to be
ashamed of, brother.

03:27.741 --> 03:30.344
I'm sorry?
Posttraumatic
stress disorder.

03:30.378 --> 03:31.579
You see, these

03:31.612 --> 03:32.846
African-American men, uh,

03:32.880 --> 03:34.615
they're the primary victims

03:34.648 --> 03:36.517
in gun violence
and they come from a culture...

03:36.550 --> 03:38.519
I-I'm sorry, I'm just gonna
jump in right there.

03:38.552 --> 03:40.220
With all due respect,

03:40.254 --> 03:41.622
you're not a doctor, Councilman,

03:41.655 --> 03:42.890
so please do not diagnose me.

03:42.923 --> 03:44.758
And-and furthermore,
as far as

03:44.792 --> 03:47.295
"victim" goes, I'm not that.

03:47.328 --> 03:49.563
If anybody's a victim,
it's actually Freda Gatz.

03:49.597 --> 03:50.964
ANGELO:
All right, well,

03:50.998 --> 03:53.033
then who put the gun
in her hands?

03:53.066 --> 03:54.802
YEE: Well, Councilman Dubois
has a point, now.

03:54.835 --> 03:56.203
How is Freda Gatz the victim?

03:56.236 --> 03:57.204
Well, then, why don't we all try

03:57.237 --> 03:58.272
to grow up where she grew up?

03:58.306 --> 04:00.474
See, it's that line of thinking

04:00.508 --> 04:01.809
that does a tremendous
disservice to black folk.

04:01.842 --> 04:03.243
Wait, I'm sorry.

04:03.277 --> 04:05.546
What-what country are we
living in? "Disservice"?

04:05.579 --> 04:07.247
It's actually not thinking;
it's a fact, Councilman.

04:07.281 --> 04:09.283
Urban, young, black children

04:09.317 --> 04:11.985
deal with poverty and racism,

04:12.019 --> 04:14.121
oppression from police
brutality itself,

04:14.154 --> 04:15.656
mass incarceration,
so how...
Understandable.

04:15.689 --> 04:17.991
How are we supposed to deal
with these circumstances

04:18.025 --> 04:19.427
if we marginalize
ourselves?

04:19.460 --> 04:21.094
Hmm.
I'll tell you how.

04:21.128 --> 04:22.563
Education.

04:22.596 --> 04:23.931
Opportunity.

04:23.964 --> 04:27.234
See, this is
what we promote

04:27.267 --> 04:29.269
in our program WOKE, all right?

04:29.303 --> 04:32.105
We Organize for Knowledge
and Empowerment.

04:32.139 --> 04:34.074
Well, Councilman,
why don't you tell Jamal Lyon

04:34.107 --> 04:36.477
how WOKE is taking on
racism and oppression?

04:36.510 --> 04:37.745
I have a better idea.

04:37.778 --> 04:39.780
Why doesn't Jamal
come and visit

04:39.813 --> 04:42.650
one of our anti-violence
summits this week?

04:42.683 --> 04:44.318
(mouthing)

04:47.688 --> 04:49.523
Come through, we'd love
to have you, sir.

04:49.557 --> 04:51.325
I'd love to.
I'm there.

04:51.359 --> 04:52.793
All right, yeah.

04:52.826 --> 04:55.162
Hmm.

04:55.195 --> 04:56.296
Jamal, what the hell
is wrong with you?

04:56.330 --> 04:57.297
Agreeing to do
some stupid summit

04:57.331 --> 04:59.367
with that bougie bitch.

04:59.400 --> 05:00.801
He wouldn't know the streets

05:00.834 --> 05:02.636
if it shot him in the ass.
Lord, I know, Ma.

05:02.670 --> 05:04.204
But you know what?
He was making sense
and you know it.

05:04.237 --> 05:06.640
You know, what you need to be
doing is making new music.

05:06.674 --> 05:08.942
See, doing that radio station
was just damage control.

05:08.976 --> 05:11.879
You need to get your ass back
onstage and prove to your fans

05:11.912 --> 05:13.514
that that brain fart
was a one-time thing.
Ma...
Ma, Ma...

05:13.547 --> 05:14.782
Excuse me, Mrs. Lyon...

05:14.815 --> 05:16.684
Ms. Lyon.
Ms. Lyon.

05:16.717 --> 05:18.285
Are you joining us
at the summit?

05:18.318 --> 05:20.454
No, I'm busy,
and so is Jamal.

05:20.488 --> 05:22.122
I guess he forgot
to tell you

05:22.155 --> 05:23.991
he's in the studio
all week.

05:24.024 --> 05:26.394
That's too bad.
The kids are huge fans of yours.

05:26.427 --> 05:27.661
As a matter of fact,

05:27.695 --> 05:29.697
they started
Snapchatting already.

05:29.730 --> 05:31.499
There we go.
Wow.

05:31.532 --> 05:32.900
ANGELO:
That one's Isaiah.

05:32.933 --> 05:34.535
He's a, uh,
he's a shining star.

05:34.568 --> 05:36.837
Mm-hmm.
Look, you know what?

05:36.870 --> 05:38.472
I'm-I'm gonna figure out
my schedule.

05:38.506 --> 05:39.707
You know, I'm not
gonna let them down.

05:39.740 --> 05:40.974
That would be great.
I appreciate that,

05:41.008 --> 05:42.075
from both of you.
Yeah, yeah.

05:42.109 --> 05:43.210
Mm-hmm.
We gotta go.

05:43.243 --> 05:44.211
I look forward
to seeing you both there.

05:44.244 --> 05:45.479
Uh-huh, bye-bye.

05:45.513 --> 05:47.214
Why you gotta
be so rude?

05:47.247 --> 05:49.249
'Cause we got
a FBI agent up our ass.

05:49.282 --> 05:50.684
We don't need
a politician, too.

05:50.718 --> 05:52.152
That man was being
so polite.

05:52.185 --> 05:53.421
I don't trust polite people,
stupid.

05:59.059 --> 06:00.394
LUCIOUS:
My Empire XStream launch

06:00.428 --> 06:02.763
might have had some difficulties

06:02.796 --> 06:05.332
had you not done
what you did.

06:05.365 --> 06:07.435
I mean, nobody's even
talking about Jamal.

06:07.468 --> 06:09.269
All anybody can talk about--

06:09.302 --> 06:11.338
the press and me alike--

06:11.371 --> 06:13.707
is this rare talent

06:13.741 --> 06:15.743
that just blew everybody away.

06:15.776 --> 06:17.611
SHINE:
You shouldn't have cut me off.

06:17.645 --> 06:20.914
We could've been making millions
with Nessa a long time ago.

06:20.948 --> 06:23.116
What I want to know is,
what do you want to do next?

06:23.150 --> 06:24.785
What's your next move?

06:24.818 --> 06:26.253
HAKEEM:
I tell you what.

06:26.286 --> 06:28.055
Me and Shine
already working on something.

06:28.088 --> 06:31.425
You know, I was thinking about
coming out with a living album,

06:31.459 --> 06:34.261
something like Yeezy with his
Life of Pablo situation.

06:34.294 --> 06:35.262
But bigger.

06:35.295 --> 06:36.564
And my homie Nessa,

06:36.597 --> 06:37.598
she gonna
help me do it,

06:37.631 --> 06:39.199
some of the tracks.

06:39.232 --> 06:40.434
Is that what you really want?

06:40.468 --> 06:42.369
With all the heat

06:42.402 --> 06:44.071
you got going on

06:44.104 --> 06:46.707
from being a part of
my Empire XStream launch,

06:46.740 --> 06:49.209
when the world is your oyster

06:49.242 --> 06:50.444
and you can put any name

06:50.478 --> 06:52.045
in your bucket list,

06:52.079 --> 06:54.381
and these are the only two
you want to work with?

06:54.414 --> 06:57.284
As far as you and
Hakeem working together,

06:57.317 --> 06:59.453
that's a whole nother
conversation.

06:59.487 --> 07:01.922
He's got an entirely new set

07:01.955 --> 07:04.257
of familial responsibilities
he's gotta handle.

07:04.291 --> 07:05.392
What's that got to do with it?

07:05.425 --> 07:06.727
LUCIOUS:
Bella's at home right now

07:06.760 --> 07:08.295
with her mother,
where you should be,

07:08.328 --> 07:11.899
but you've got
a convenient case of amnesia.

07:11.932 --> 07:13.634
But we're gonna talk
about that in private,

07:13.667 --> 07:14.968
'cause me and Shine...

07:15.002 --> 07:17.538
we got business to take care of.

07:19.640 --> 07:21.642
*

07:26.647 --> 07:29.517
You can keep
your fancy espresso machine,

07:29.550 --> 07:31.819
you can keep
your little fancy

07:31.852 --> 07:33.420
wine fridge...

07:33.453 --> 07:34.988
You know what?
Lucious, please,

07:35.022 --> 07:36.757
keep all of
this stuff, okay?

07:36.790 --> 07:40.027
In fact, give this to your wife.

07:40.060 --> 07:42.295
What are you trying
to do, impress me?

07:42.329 --> 07:44.632
You know I can buy
all of this stuff myself.

07:44.665 --> 07:45.866
All right, well,
why don't you just tell me

07:45.899 --> 07:47.100
what it is you need?

07:47.134 --> 07:48.936
What I need

07:48.969 --> 07:51.271
is for you to respect
my boundaries.

07:51.304 --> 07:52.806
Stop it with
all of this, Lucious,

07:52.840 --> 07:54.141
'cause it's not working.

07:54.174 --> 07:55.375
You handle
the business,

07:55.408 --> 07:56.644
I handle the music.

07:56.677 --> 07:57.878
That, and my three sons,

07:57.911 --> 07:59.379
that's all we need to discuss.

07:59.412 --> 08:01.949
Fine. From here on,
it's strictly business.

08:01.982 --> 08:03.216
Strictly business.

08:03.250 --> 08:05.452
Well, businesswise,

08:05.485 --> 08:07.655
you might want to come by
and see me later.

08:07.688 --> 08:09.523
Maybe you can take
a look at the artwork

08:09.557 --> 08:11.792
for Jamal's
Black and White album.

08:11.825 --> 08:13.661
Uh, Jamal doesn't want
to release

08:13.694 --> 08:15.295
the Black and White album.

08:15.328 --> 08:16.897
You know that,
Lucious.
Yeah, well,

08:16.930 --> 08:18.331
it's not about
what Jamal wants.

08:18.365 --> 08:20.801
Empire XStream
needs content.

08:20.834 --> 08:23.370
And Jamal needs for
his fans to forget about

08:23.403 --> 08:24.705
his little fainting,

08:24.738 --> 08:26.039
Justin Bieber moment.
Look,

08:26.073 --> 08:27.507
Tiana has a record

08:27.541 --> 08:28.909
that will be ready
by the end of the month.

08:28.942 --> 08:31.044
J Poppa's on his way
back from his tour,

08:31.078 --> 08:33.480
and V's single
is about to drop,

08:33.513 --> 08:34.815
so, there,
content.

08:34.848 --> 08:36.049
See, that's why
I love you.

08:36.083 --> 08:37.150
You're just amazing.

08:37.184 --> 08:38.418
Look,

08:38.451 --> 08:40.220
I mean that in
a strictly business way.

08:40.253 --> 08:41.488
Yeah. Right.

08:41.521 --> 08:42.890
I see you kept the gun.

08:45.125 --> 08:46.727
Bye, Fuh-Lucious.

08:46.760 --> 08:48.862
Nobody got time
for your mess.

08:50.731 --> 08:52.099
(sighs)

08:52.132 --> 08:53.801
They'll all come around.

08:58.071 --> 08:59.272
JAMAL:
Uh, over here,

08:59.306 --> 09:00.273
these are the recording studios.

09:00.307 --> 09:01.575
We'll go over there
in a little bit.

09:01.609 --> 09:04.544
This is where every single
Empire artist records.

09:04.578 --> 09:05.545
Um, that's the boardroom.

09:05.579 --> 09:07.047
They look like
they working;

09:07.080 --> 09:09.016
they not really
working.
(laughs)

09:09.049 --> 09:10.117
Oh, snap!
That's Lucious Lyon!

09:10.150 --> 09:11.518
Dad!

09:11.551 --> 09:13.553
Dad, wait, hold up.

09:15.088 --> 09:17.057
This is Councilman
Angelo Dubois.

09:17.090 --> 09:19.026
Mr. Lyon,
it's a pleasure.

09:19.059 --> 09:20.260
Oh, it's all mine.

09:20.293 --> 09:21.629
All right, all right.

09:21.662 --> 09:22.930
Mom and I met him
today at Power 105,

09:22.963 --> 09:24.431
so I'm kind of helping out

09:24.464 --> 09:25.866
with the anti-violence summit
with the kids.

09:25.899 --> 09:27.267
I'm Zeah,
Mr. Lyon.

09:27.300 --> 09:28.535
I'm gonna be an MC,
just like you.

09:28.568 --> 09:29.569
Want to hear something?

09:31.171 --> 09:33.273
Okay, go on ahead,
man, sure.

09:33.306 --> 09:34.975
All right, check.

09:35.008 --> 09:37.310
* First off, my main purpose
is to change the game *

09:37.344 --> 09:39.546
* Before I let you go,
bet you all know my name *

09:39.579 --> 09:42.249
* They call me Zey,
bet on me, catch a payday *

09:42.282 --> 09:44.885
* See, I'm a leader,
my flow cold, so grab a heater *

09:44.918 --> 09:47.287
* Before I let you go, OG,
it's great to meet you. *

09:47.320 --> 09:48.989
Ah!
(all cheering)

09:49.022 --> 09:50.557
(chuckling):
You had me nervous for a second.

09:50.590 --> 09:52.292
Man, I thought you was
coming straight for me.

09:52.325 --> 09:53.827
Nah, nah, nah, nah.

09:53.861 --> 09:55.562
But we might have
to put you in the studio,

09:55.595 --> 09:57.898
seeing that Jamal
no longer makes music

09:57.931 --> 09:59.499
because he wants
to save the world.

09:59.532 --> 10:01.434
My dad likes
to come for me a lot,

10:01.468 --> 10:03.103
and it gets
very boring.
(chuckles)

10:03.136 --> 10:04.838
Besides, you're
missing the point.

10:04.872 --> 10:06.406
I'm now making music

10:06.439 --> 10:08.575
in order to save
the world.
All right.

10:08.608 --> 10:10.944
Zeah here's off
to MIT next year.

10:10.978 --> 10:12.646
3.8 GPA.

10:12.680 --> 10:14.314
Wow, that's impressive.

10:14.347 --> 10:16.416
You say your mama's
into this, right?

10:16.449 --> 10:18.085
I mean, I'm the one
that's on the panel.

10:18.118 --> 10:19.987
So why don't
we just hold the summit

10:20.020 --> 10:21.421
right here at Empire?

10:21.454 --> 10:22.589
(kids exclaiming)
Oh.

10:22.622 --> 10:23.824
Mr. Lyon, please...

10:23.857 --> 10:25.859
No, Lucious. Please.

10:25.893 --> 10:27.761
ANGELO:
I appreciate that,

10:27.795 --> 10:29.496
but we're good.

10:29.529 --> 10:31.164
We have a spot secured already;
the kids are excited...

10:31.198 --> 10:32.599
Well, why don't I
sweeten the deal

10:32.632 --> 10:35.535
and say Empire underwrites
the whole thing?

10:35.568 --> 10:37.671
Uh...

10:37.705 --> 10:38.939
Put me in an awkward...

10:38.972 --> 10:40.340
What do you think, kids?

10:40.373 --> 10:41.608
KIDS:
Yes!
Well, okay.

10:41.641 --> 10:42.843
There you have it.

10:42.876 --> 10:44.111
(chuckles)
It's a very,

10:44.144 --> 10:45.813
very generous offer,
Lucious.

10:45.846 --> 10:47.214
Thank you.
Extremely generous, Dad.

10:47.247 --> 10:49.449
What is this about?
Look, why don't we

10:49.482 --> 10:51.952
stream this whole thing live
on Empire XStream?

10:51.985 --> 10:53.553
(laughing)
I mean,
you've read about it

10:53.586 --> 10:55.622
and there's no better way
of getting your message out.

10:55.655 --> 10:57.490
Oh. Wow. You are
truly an angel, sir.

10:57.524 --> 10:58.959
Appreciate this.

