23:59.005 --> 24:00.973
Good.

24:01.007 --> 24:03.943
'Cause I'm about
to make her mine.

24:03.976 --> 24:05.545
So watch your mouth.

24:06.879 --> 24:08.848
* This ain't a blast
from the past... *

24:08.881 --> 24:10.382
(chuckles)

24:12.785 --> 24:15.354
I swear, I must have sat out

24:15.387 --> 24:18.157
in front of that water ice shop

24:18.190 --> 24:20.292
for, like, two and a half hours

24:20.326 --> 24:22.328
just hoping
and waiting for...

24:22.361 --> 24:24.597
to get my little
rap right, so by the time

24:24.631 --> 24:27.133
you decided to come out, I would
be able to spit something

24:27.166 --> 24:29.435
that you might like.
So you knew I
had a boyfriend

24:29.468 --> 24:31.771
and you still
tried to get at me?
No.

24:31.804 --> 24:33.439
I knew that it was a long shot.

24:33.472 --> 24:35.441
I knew that you was this

24:35.474 --> 24:37.443
Catholic, studious girl...

24:37.476 --> 24:39.879
hanging out with some nerd.

24:39.912 --> 24:41.814
And why would a girl like you

24:41.848 --> 24:43.716
want to talk
to somebody like me?
Barry

24:43.750 --> 24:46.619
was not a nerd.
No, but he wasn't a gangster.

24:46.653 --> 24:48.320
That was me, all day long.

24:48.354 --> 24:51.123
And that's what I was,
and you knew that.

24:51.157 --> 24:52.792
You knew that was
what I was about,

24:52.825 --> 24:54.727
but instead of running,
you stuck around.

24:54.761 --> 24:56.462
Yeah, well, I was
young and simple.

24:56.495 --> 24:58.565
I should've
stayed with Barry.

24:58.598 --> 25:00.833
I'm serious, Cookie.

25:00.867 --> 25:04.403
You saw me in those streets
and you knew...

25:04.436 --> 25:07.807
that that wasn't my destiny.

25:07.840 --> 25:10.209
You knew that my destiny
was music

25:10.242 --> 25:13.079
and my destiny was you.

25:20.920 --> 25:22.388
How'd you do it?

25:24.223 --> 25:25.725
How'd I do what?

25:27.293 --> 25:29.996
I don't know anybody
who lost more than you.

25:30.029 --> 25:31.998
And you survived it,

25:32.031 --> 25:34.767
and you're-you're still here,
you're still fighting.

25:37.236 --> 25:39.238
You're a fighter, too, Andre.

25:39.271 --> 25:42.541
I mean, after I met
your grandmother,

25:42.575 --> 25:45.778
everything makes sense now.
And I admire you even more.

25:45.812 --> 25:48.347
I mean, Andre, look at
what all you've accomplished.

25:48.380 --> 25:50.382
Yeah, look where
that got me, Mama.

25:52.551 --> 25:54.787
You sure you don't want
to go back to church, baby?

25:54.821 --> 25:57.356
Oh.
Huh? Yeah. And, um...

25:57.389 --> 25:59.091
clear your mind, heal your soul.

25:59.125 --> 26:00.526
So much is...
What soul?

26:00.559 --> 26:01.861
Don't say that, And...

26:01.894 --> 26:04.764
What soul?

26:04.797 --> 26:06.398
Look, come here.
Sit down.

26:08.500 --> 26:09.969
I'm proud of you.

26:10.002 --> 26:11.971
No, no, no, no, no--

26:12.004 --> 26:13.806
I'm proud of you, Andre.

26:13.840 --> 26:17.476
Didn't nobody have no summits
for you when I got locked away.

26:17.509 --> 26:19.578
You figured it out
all on your own.

26:19.612 --> 26:21.480
You fought your way
out of the hood, baby,

26:21.513 --> 26:25.151
you got yourself into
Wharton. You did that.

26:25.184 --> 26:27.253
Against all obstacles.

26:27.286 --> 26:29.956
Against everything this world
throws at black people,

26:29.989 --> 26:33.926
you fought your way out.

26:33.960 --> 26:36.395
Keep fighting.

26:36.428 --> 26:40.099
Please, okay?

26:40.132 --> 26:41.801
'Cause I got you.

26:41.834 --> 26:43.736
I got you, no matter what.

26:43.770 --> 26:44.837
No matter what?

26:44.871 --> 26:47.106
No matter what, baby.

26:48.675 --> 26:51.410
(shuddering breath)

26:51.443 --> 26:52.679
You gonna be all right, baby.

26:52.712 --> 26:54.714
Okay.
Yes.

26:56.148 --> 26:58.785
Okay.
Okay.

26:58.818 --> 27:01.120
*

27:03.823 --> 27:06.358
See, on the trill I was thinking
I come back right here,

27:06.392 --> 27:08.427
drop some ad-libs
for a bar, man.

27:08.460 --> 27:10.529
Okay, yeah.
I say do it for two bars--

27:10.562 --> 27:12.464
it's gonna build the
anticipation for the hook,

27:12.498 --> 27:14.100
and that's gonna make it hard.

27:14.133 --> 27:15.367
Yeah, I agree.

27:15.401 --> 27:17.036
It needs to come harder.
Yeah.

27:17.069 --> 27:18.771
(music stops)
Or maybe we drop everything

27:18.805 --> 27:20.506
and keep
the bass line.

27:20.539 --> 27:22.541
Yeah?
SHINE: Yeah.

27:22.574 --> 27:24.610
Yeah, I think
you're on to something.

27:24.643 --> 27:26.012
All right, then.

27:26.045 --> 27:28.014
Hey, stand up for me, homie.

27:28.047 --> 27:29.648
Where'd you put
that bass channel I...

27:29.682 --> 27:31.150
(grunts)

27:33.419 --> 27:34.821
You must be out your
rabbit-ass mind,

27:34.854 --> 27:36.856
lookin' at my sister
like that.

27:39.859 --> 27:41.828
Think I'm playing?

27:41.861 --> 27:43.562
He'll be all right.

27:43.595 --> 27:45.297
Okay...

27:45.331 --> 27:47.700
what was you saying, Hakeem?

27:55.341 --> 27:56.709
* They don't wanna see us
make it *
* But we still gonna make it *

27:56.743 --> 27:57.910
* That's why
they always hatin' *

27:57.944 --> 27:59.178
* Why they always hating *

27:59.211 --> 28:01.313
* They don't really want
to see us win *

28:01.347 --> 28:04.350
* They rather see us dead
or in the pen *
* Watch out, watch out *

28:04.383 --> 28:07.386
* They don't wanna
see us make it *
* But we still gonna make it *

28:07.419 --> 28:10.389
* That's why we gonna make it
* Why they always hatin' *

28:10.422 --> 28:11.690
* Don't you know that
you was born to win? *

28:11.724 --> 28:13.159
* All you gotta do is stay up

28:13.192 --> 28:15.494
* Out the pen, stay awake
and watch out *

28:15.527 --> 28:17.930
* I'm tired of seeing
people dying *

28:17.964 --> 28:21.100
* On the news
all I see is crying *
* I swear I can't take it *

28:21.133 --> 28:23.035
* I need to see
my people trying *

28:23.069 --> 28:25.537
* In the jungle
just roll with the lions *

28:25.571 --> 28:28.674
* Just roll with a lion *
* 'Cause it's a jungle
out there, boy, it's a jungle *

28:28.707 --> 28:30.877
* It's a jungle *
* And they don't want you to
grow, they want to stunt you *

28:30.910 --> 28:33.780
* They wanna leave you back *
* We need to start
raising the bar *

28:33.813 --> 28:37.716
* Dream big
and just reach for the stars *
* All you gotta do is reach *

28:37.750 --> 28:40.186
* They don't wanna see us make
it *
* But we still gonna make it *

28:40.219 --> 28:42.688
* That's why we gonna make it
* Why they always hatin'? *

28:42.721 --> 28:44.757
* Don't you know that you was
born to win? *

28:44.791 --> 28:46.625
* All you gotta do
is stay up out the pen *

28:46.658 --> 28:48.560
* Stay awake and watch out.

28:48.594 --> 28:50.096
(cheering and applause)

28:50.129 --> 28:51.263
ANGELO:
Yes.

28:51.297 --> 28:53.199
Yes, yes.

28:53.232 --> 28:56.168
Thank you, young Zeah.

28:58.337 --> 29:00.139
And now let me introduce to you

29:00.172 --> 29:02.308
our guest of honor.

29:02.341 --> 29:04.243
Jamal Lyon.

29:04.276 --> 29:06.745
(cheering and applause)

29:09.816 --> 29:11.483
He himself a victim...

29:14.020 --> 29:15.721
(clears throat)

29:15.754 --> 29:17.890
Excuse me.

29:17.924 --> 29:20.726
I'm going to replace
the word "victim"

29:20.759 --> 29:22.661
with "survivor."
Yes.

29:22.694 --> 29:24.797
(applause)
Yes, survivor.

29:24.831 --> 29:26.132
Jamal Lyon,

29:26.165 --> 29:28.801
he himself a survivor
of gun violence.

29:28.835 --> 29:30.136
You see, these young men...

29:30.169 --> 29:32.238
Look, I know he
get on your nerves,

29:32.271 --> 29:33.840
but he is fine.

29:33.873 --> 29:35.507
ANGELO: ...they all come from
a place where violence

29:35.541 --> 29:37.309
is a natural go-to.

29:37.343 --> 29:40.412
But our goal is not
to save the world.

29:40.446 --> 29:44.750
Our goal is to pull them
upwards from violence

29:44.783 --> 29:47.319
and move them onward
to success.

29:47.353 --> 29:49.155
(applause)

29:49.188 --> 29:51.757
That was good,
though, wasn't it?

29:51.790 --> 29:53.692
Look, you look full, don't you?
(laughs)

29:57.163 --> 29:59.031
Hey, man, here you go.

29:59.065 --> 30:00.432
Thank you, thank you, man!

30:00.466 --> 30:02.835
Uh-uh, I'm keeping mine.

30:02.869 --> 30:05.437
Candace would kill me if I
didn't save her some crab legs.

30:05.471 --> 30:07.874
Most of 'em
are crackheads anyway.

30:07.907 --> 30:09.541
Well, maybe they
wouldn't be if someone

30:09.575 --> 30:11.777
had shared their crab
legs a little sooner.

30:11.810 --> 30:15.147
What are you,
Mr. Save-the-World now?

30:15.181 --> 30:16.448
With you by my side.

30:16.482 --> 30:18.650
By the time you
finish up at Howard,

30:18.684 --> 30:20.286
I'll be getting
out of med school

30:20.319 --> 30:21.787
and I can set up a practice

30:21.820 --> 30:25.357
in King of Prussia.

30:25.391 --> 30:26.993
All right,
forget King of Prussia...

30:27.026 --> 30:30.729
Look, Barry, stop.

30:30.762 --> 30:33.632
I'm-a be honest, a'ight?

30:33.665 --> 30:37.169
At some point, I want
the house and the kids

30:37.203 --> 30:38.905
and all that stuff that
you say, but right now?

30:38.938 --> 30:40.739
I don't know what I want

30:40.772 --> 30:43.910
except I know it's got
something to do with music.

30:43.943 --> 30:45.677
And I don't want to
feel locked down

30:45.711 --> 30:47.179
before I even give it a shot.

30:47.213 --> 30:51.017
Ya'mean?

30:51.050 --> 30:53.252
I understand, Loretha.

30:53.285 --> 30:55.054
It's your life.

30:55.087 --> 30:58.124
You won't get a second chance
to live it the way you want.

31:01.227 --> 31:02.561
ANGELO:
Now, yesterday

31:02.594 --> 31:05.597
I got chin-checked
by a remarkable woman

31:05.631 --> 31:07.833
who taught me the difference

31:07.866 --> 31:10.569
between being
a victim of circumstance

31:10.602 --> 31:13.339
and a survivor of
immeasurable pain.

31:13.372 --> 31:15.207
I have a feeling

31:15.241 --> 31:17.276
I'll be thanking
her over and over

31:17.309 --> 31:20.846
and over for that insight.

31:20.879 --> 31:22.949
Now I'd like to
bring up here onstage

31:22.982 --> 31:25.451
a man who is
a new friend of WOKE.

31:25.484 --> 31:28.620
The incredible Lucious Lyon.

31:28.654 --> 31:30.389
(cheering and applause)

31:38.830 --> 31:41.233
Thank you, Angelo.

31:43.335 --> 31:45.804
I'm very proud of these
young men and women here.

31:45.837 --> 31:48.440
You guys represent our future.

31:48.474 --> 31:52.211
And we are looking to you
to be great leaders.

31:52.244 --> 31:53.912
I have my son here.

31:53.946 --> 31:55.414
And as you all know,

31:55.447 --> 31:58.084
he almost lost his life

31:58.117 --> 31:59.751
trying to save my own.

31:59.785 --> 32:01.320
(applause)

32:07.026 --> 32:10.462
Now I know we all want to get to
the talking part of this summit,

32:10.496 --> 32:12.098
but before we do that,

32:12.131 --> 32:14.233
why don't we take a moment

32:14.266 --> 32:16.435
and have Jamal Lyon

32:16.468 --> 32:18.504
come up here and do a song,

32:18.537 --> 32:21.140
'cause he has not performed
since that event at the ASAs.

32:21.173 --> 32:22.408
And I think this would be

32:22.441 --> 32:24.910
a most fitting moment for him.

32:24.943 --> 32:26.312
(cheering and applause)

32:31.550 --> 32:32.751
Jamal. Jamal.

32:32.784 --> 32:33.986
Jamal.

32:34.020 --> 32:36.788
Jamal. Jamal. Jamal.

32:36.822 --> 32:38.024
ALL (chanting):
Jamal! Jamal!

32:38.057 --> 32:40.792
Jamal! Jamal! Jamal! Jamal!

32:40.826 --> 32:44.830
Jamal! Jamal! Jamal!
Jamal! Jamal! Jamal!

32:44.863 --> 32:47.266
Jamal! Jamal! Jamal!

32:47.299 --> 32:50.436
Jamal! Jamal! Jamal! Jamal!

32:50.469 --> 32:53.672
Jamal! Jamal!
Jamal! Jamal!

32:53.705 --> 32:56.175
Jamal! Jamal! Jamal! Jamal!

32:56.208 --> 32:58.677
(heavy breathing)

32:58.710 --> 33:00.612
(exhales heavily)

33:00.646 --> 33:02.648
(breathing heavily)

33:06.085 --> 33:07.353
(exhales shakily)

33:12.691 --> 33:13.925
(breathing heavily)

33:16.728 --> 33:18.697
Jamal.

33:18.730 --> 33:19.965
What are you doing?

33:19.998 --> 33:21.167
Huh?

33:21.200 --> 33:22.468
What's going on?

33:22.501 --> 33:24.570
(gasping)

33:24.603 --> 33:25.471
What the hell
is wrong with you?

33:25.504 --> 33:27.239
What he need to do

33:27.273 --> 33:28.907
is get his ass on that stage.

33:28.940 --> 33:30.042
'Cause the only way

33:30.076 --> 33:32.044
to deal with a problem, boy,

33:32.078 --> 33:33.679
is to deal with a problem.

33:33.712 --> 33:34.913
It keeps happening.
Shh, all right.

33:34.946 --> 33:36.382
It keeps happening.

33:36.415 --> 33:37.716
You really starting
to bore me, boy.

33:37.749 --> 33:38.984
I'm scared, all right?!

33:39.017 --> 33:40.186
That's what you want, right?

33:40.219 --> 33:41.353
(gasping)

33:44.022 --> 33:45.924
Well, yeah, I got a,
I got a pro-- I got a problem

33:45.957 --> 33:47.359
and I...

33:47.393 --> 33:49.228
can't get onstage.

33:51.263 --> 33:53.265
I can't...
I can't do it no more.

34:07.079 --> 34:09.081
*

34:09.115 --> 34:10.349
Yeah!

34:10.382 --> 34:12.518
(indistinct chatter)

34:12.551 --> 34:14.086
You were right.

34:14.120 --> 34:15.921
Jamal has a problem.

34:15.954 --> 34:18.023
So, what we gonna
do to fix it?

34:18.056 --> 34:20.025
I don't think

34:20.058 --> 34:21.627
this is something you need
to be smiling about.

34:21.660 --> 34:24.096
Well, you said the magic word.

34:24.130 --> 34:26.932
It's "we."

34:26.965 --> 34:28.900
I mean, that's how
it's always been,

34:28.934 --> 34:30.302
Lucious and Cookie,
you know?

34:30.336 --> 34:31.303
You and me against

34:31.337 --> 34:33.305
this crazy-ass world and...

34:33.339 --> 34:35.141
us versus everybody else.

34:35.174 --> 34:36.542
Excuse my interruption.

34:36.575 --> 34:38.210
I'm sorry.

34:38.244 --> 34:40.312
I just wanted to thank you both
for today.

34:40.346 --> 34:42.881
We couldn't have done it
without both of your support.

34:42.914 --> 34:45.217
You know, a lot of these kids,
they come from broken homes.

34:45.251 --> 34:47.786
You know, uh, divorce,
separation...

34:47.819 --> 34:49.721
Some parents never even...
(chuckles)

34:49.755 --> 34:51.123
...were together
in the first place.

34:51.157 --> 34:53.292
So it just
means a lot

34:53.325 --> 34:54.893
to have these kids
see you two

34:54.926 --> 34:57.129
together, getting along
even though

34:57.163 --> 34:59.097
you're not married
anymore.

34:59.131 --> 35:00.332
It's truly amazing.

35:00.366 --> 35:01.933
Black love. It's beautiful.

35:01.967 --> 35:03.469
"Black love..."

35:03.502 --> 35:04.970
Tell me something,
Councilman.

35:05.003 --> 35:06.172
Sir.

35:06.205 --> 35:08.574
Are you from a "broken family"?
No.

35:08.607 --> 35:09.808
No, not at all.

35:09.841 --> 35:11.510
My parents been together
50 years.

35:11.543 --> 35:12.944
50 years.
Wow, that...
Yeah.

35:12.978 --> 35:14.480
...that is something.
It's a blessing.

35:14.513 --> 35:15.514
Lucious and I ain't together.

35:15.547 --> 35:17.649
ANGELO: Oh.
Mm-mm, no.

35:17.683 --> 35:22.321
But we've been
ride or die for...

35:22.354 --> 35:25.924
Well, if I tell you that,
I'd be telling you my age.

35:25.957 --> 35:27.193
(both chuckle)
Ms. Lyon...

35:27.226 --> 35:29.094
Oh, no, Cookie.
(giggles)

35:29.127 --> 35:30.262
Well, Cookie...

35:30.296 --> 35:32.030
uh, you should come down
to the center sometime

35:32.063 --> 35:33.499
and speak to
the young women.

35:33.532 --> 35:34.800
I think they'd, uh,

35:34.833 --> 35:35.867
they'd get a kick
out of that.

35:35.901 --> 35:37.303
Well, you should
invite me over.

35:37.336 --> 35:38.770
I will.
I will, then, Cookie.

35:38.804 --> 35:40.539
Yes.
Lucious...

35:40.572 --> 35:43.309
Thanks again, man.

35:46.245 --> 35:49.181
I think you had it right
the first time.

35:49.215 --> 35:51.049
It's Mr. Lyon.

36:01.159 --> 36:03.662
*

36:05.397 --> 36:06.632
Mmm...
(gasps)

36:06.665 --> 36:07.899
(laughs)

36:07.933 --> 36:09.401
You scare me!

36:09.435 --> 36:10.769
I got good news.

36:13.739 --> 36:14.973
Good news?

36:15.006 --> 36:16.208
I love good news.
Tell me.

36:16.242 --> 36:18.043
I'm leaving Empire.

36:19.678 --> 36:21.046
How is that good news?

36:21.079 --> 36:22.814
'Cause I got
a offer from Vaughn.

36:22.848 --> 36:24.350
(scoffs)

36:24.383 --> 36:26.252
Hell, Lucious just
had him at the house.

36:26.285 --> 36:27.753
He's a snake.
What's the offer?

36:27.786 --> 36:30.922
Yo, it's a hell
of an offer, Beck.

36:30.956 --> 36:32.324
And the best
part about it...

36:32.358 --> 36:34.726
I negotiated for you
to come with me.

36:34.760 --> 36:36.862
Who asked you to do that?

36:36.895 --> 36:38.730
Lucious and Cookie
make you head of A&R yet?

36:38.764 --> 36:40.599
We are talking about it.

36:41.867 --> 36:44.403
The word on the street...

36:44.436 --> 36:46.272
is that they're looking
for somebody new.

36:48.307 --> 36:50.342
It's time for you
to bail, mama.

36:50.376 --> 36:52.578
You need to be somewhere
where you appreciated.

36:54.212 --> 36:57.783
And we make a dope-ass team,
Becky with the Good Hair.

36:57.816 --> 37:00.051
That's real talk.

37:00.085 --> 37:01.687
You know, Lucious gave me a job

37:01.720 --> 37:03.422
when no one else
would even talk to me.

37:03.455 --> 37:05.257
That's real talk.
I'm not doing this thing.

37:05.291 --> 37:07.259
Come on, this place
is going down in flames,

37:07.293 --> 37:09.194
you know that.
What are you
talking about?

37:09.227 --> 37:11.530
We got hits across the board.
You sound stupid right now.

37:11.563 --> 37:13.031
I'm not talking
about music!

37:13.064 --> 37:14.466
The feds is gonna come

37:14.500 --> 37:15.901
and they're gonna start
knocking the doors

37:15.934 --> 37:17.603
all down and around
this place.

37:17.636 --> 37:18.870
I love you, okay?

37:18.904 --> 37:20.406
I love you.

37:20.439 --> 37:22.073
But I'm not
letting my career

37:22.107 --> 37:23.942
go down with
this building.

37:23.975 --> 37:25.844
And you shouldn't either.

37:28.280 --> 37:30.282
*

37:36.288 --> 37:38.123
Not sure you should be
mixing those with Scotch.

37:39.858 --> 37:41.660
I sure am doing it
tonight, though.

37:41.693 --> 37:42.961
(chuckles)

37:45.263 --> 37:47.098
Been lying to myself,
y'all, 'cause...

37:49.267 --> 37:51.903
Walking around, acting
like everything's cool,

37:51.937 --> 37:53.138
just managing
a little pain,

37:53.171 --> 37:55.240
but...

37:55.273 --> 37:57.776
When I was up on the stage
at the Empire XStream event,

37:57.809 --> 38:01.513
I could see the lights
just flashing, flashing...

38:03.882 --> 38:05.116
And then Freda.

38:09.321 --> 38:10.922
It was wack.

38:10.956 --> 38:13.024
PTSD.

38:13.058 --> 38:14.460
Man...

38:14.493 --> 38:16.261
everybody messed up.

38:16.294 --> 38:19.598
Ain't nobody as messed up as
the Lyon brothers, I'm sorry.

38:19.631 --> 38:21.533
(all chuckling)

38:21.567 --> 38:23.902
But you know what we got
that nobody else does?

38:25.036 --> 38:26.304
We got each other.

38:28.306 --> 38:30.008
So here is how we win.

38:30.041 --> 38:32.344
Jamal... you gonna
beat this.

38:33.311 --> 38:34.680
Say it.

38:34.713 --> 38:36.114
I'm gonna beat this.

38:36.147 --> 38:37.383
Say it like you mean it.
Come on, man.

38:37.416 --> 38:38.650
I'm gonna beat this.

38:38.684 --> 38:40.118
You're back onstage
in no time.

38:40.151 --> 38:41.520
Hakeem...

38:42.854 --> 38:45.290
...you're a father.

38:45.323 --> 38:47.258
First of the Lyon sons.

38:49.395 --> 38:50.862
If you're ready
to step up,

38:50.896 --> 38:52.864
we got your back.

38:52.898 --> 38:54.299
You ready?

38:54.332 --> 38:56.034
I'm ready.

38:56.067 --> 38:57.235
ANDRE:
Say it again.

38:57.268 --> 38:58.804
I'm ready.

38:58.837 --> 39:00.406
Say it like a man, son.
You ready?

39:00.439 --> 39:02.073
I'm ready.
Yeah, my man.

39:02.107 --> 39:03.509
To Baby Bella.

39:03.542 --> 39:04.810
To Bella.

39:04.843 --> 39:06.878
To my daughter.

39:06.912 --> 39:08.847
To Ma.

39:11.617 --> 39:12.851
Mm-hmm, mm-hmm.

39:12.884 --> 39:14.119
Ah...

39:16.254 --> 39:17.623
HAKEEM:
What about you, Dre?

39:22.694 --> 39:23.929
Rhonda.

39:25.764 --> 39:27.365
I gotta get her out of my head.

39:27.399 --> 39:28.600
(inhales)

39:28.634 --> 39:30.502
So tomorrow,

39:30.536 --> 39:32.337
I'm gonna go
to our old place

39:32.370 --> 39:35.240
and I'm grabbing
the last of my stuff.

39:35.273 --> 39:37.543
*

39:41.780 --> 39:43.782
(distant siren wailing,
neighbors shouting faintly)

39:56.662 --> 39:58.764
* And you said
he's just a friend *

39:58.797 --> 40:01.366
* And you said he's just
a friend *

40:01.399 --> 40:03.569
* Oh, baby...
How many times
I got to tell you

40:03.602 --> 40:05.437
to stay away from that boy?

40:05.471 --> 40:06.772
But, Ma, you said
he's my brother.

40:06.805 --> 40:08.039
Tariq, you listen to me.

40:08.073 --> 40:10.408
You do not ever, ever

40:10.442 --> 40:13.745
say that out loud again,
not to anybody.

40:13.779 --> 40:15.313
Least of all to him.

40:15.346 --> 40:18.049
He may be
your half brother,

40:18.083 --> 40:19.284
but he is
not your friend.

40:19.317 --> 40:22.087
Him and his crazy-ass mama

40:22.120 --> 40:24.089
are the worst thing
that ever happened to us.

40:44.710 --> 40:45.977
(Bella fusses)

40:54.452 --> 40:56.454
(static crackles)

41:00.191 --> 41:02.193
(static crackles)

41:12.538 --> 41:14.540
(static crackles)

41:16.407 --> 41:18.009
(static crackles)

41:19.344 --> 41:20.579
(static crackles)

41:22.848 --> 41:24.850
(static crackles)

41:26.518 --> 41:27.753
(static crackles)

41:40.999 --> 41:44.135
You know what
I was thinking?

41:44.169 --> 41:47.305
We got all these
beautiful stuffed animals

41:47.338 --> 41:49.975
for our little girl.

41:50.008 --> 41:52.477
What in the world
are we doing with

41:52.510 --> 41:54.112
this thirsty-looking bear?

41:59.851 --> 42:03.454
Let's get Bella something
more befitting a princess.

42:04.355 --> 42:06.091
(static crackles)

42:09.695 --> 42:12.197
(exhales)

42:12.230 --> 42:14.232
*

42:22.473 --> 42:24.375
(tires screech, siren whoops)

42:28.079 --> 42:29.380
Hey, Officer.

42:29.414 --> 42:31.082
Step away from the car.

42:31.116 --> 42:32.618
Oh, no. No, sir,
I live right there.

42:32.651 --> 42:33.885
I mean I, uh,

42:33.919 --> 42:35.186
I used to live
right there.

42:35.220 --> 42:37.355
Lot of break-ins
in this neighborhood.

42:37.388 --> 42:38.724
You know anything about that?

42:45.163 --> 42:46.732
No, Officer, I don't know
anything about that.

42:46.765 --> 42:48.433
Why would I know
anything about that?

42:48.466 --> 42:50.535
What are you doing around here?
Like I told you,

42:50.568 --> 42:52.070
I used to live right there.

42:52.103 --> 42:54.305
Got any ID on you, yo?

42:59.144 --> 43:01.579
My wallet's in my car...

43:01.613 --> 43:03.014
yo.

43:04.349 --> 43:05.450
Oh, so you're a smartass, then.

43:05.483 --> 43:06.785
Huh. Smartass, okay.

43:06.818 --> 43:08.486
I'm moving, okay? I'm moving.
Hands on the vehicle.

43:08.519 --> 43:10.121
I don't have time for this.
Hey... would you
listen to me?

43:10.155 --> 43:11.657
Get your hands off me, man!

43:11.690 --> 43:12.891
(grunting)

43:12.924 --> 43:14.392
Hands behind
your back!
Ah!

43:14.425 --> 43:16.061
Stop resisting!

43:16.094 --> 43:18.930
You have the right to remain
silent. Anything you say...

43:18.964 --> 43:20.766
(Andre screaming)

43:20.799 --> 43:21.800
You're resisting, boy.

43:21.833 --> 43:24.970
Anything you say can
and will be used against you.

44:00.038 --> 44:01.039
Yeah.

44:05.476 --> 44:07.145
ANNOUNCER: You've just
watched Empire.

44:07.178 --> 44:09.915
Now here are a few more shows
to check out from Fox.

44:11.649 --> 44:13.719
Do you two have any idea
what this number is?

44:13.752 --> 44:16.154
-Last night's winning Lotto.
-The number of cats
in your apartment.

44:16.187 --> 44:20.992
It's the amount of money
you two cost the city
working together for three days.

44:21.026 --> 44:23.594
You've been on the job 25 years.
Not a nick on you.

44:24.730 --> 44:26.531
You get partnered with Riggs
three days,

44:26.564 --> 44:29.467
you crashed two cars
and nearly got yourself killed.

44:29.500 --> 44:33.338
-You ever feel like you made
the wrong career choice?
-Yeah, the day I met you.

44:33.371 --> 44:36.141
ANNOUNCER:
Lethal Weapon. Wednesdays.

44:36.174 --> 44:38.576
Man, take
the damn shades off!

44:38.609 --> 44:40.211
Man, put the damn shades
back on.

44:40.245 --> 44:41.112
On Fox.
